This is a common .NET MAUI pain point. `adjustResize` was deprecated by Android (API 30+) and MAUI's platform-specific helper for it no longer works reliably. The modern fix uses Android's **WindowInsets API** to detect the keyboard height and adjust your layout.

### Quick fix — two steps:

**1. `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`** — listen for IME insets:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Platform;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Android.OS.Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Let the app draw behind system bars so insets are reported
        WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window!, false);

        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(Window!.DecorView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Use whichever is taller — keyboard or nav bar
            int bottomPx = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);

            // Apply padding so content is pushed above the keyboard
            v.SetPadding(v.PaddingLeft, v.PaddingTop, v.PaddingRight, bottomPx);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

**2. Remove the old code** — delete any calls to:
```csharp
// ❌ Remove this — no longer effective
App.Current.On<Android>()
   .UseWindowSoftInputModeAdjust(WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize);
```

### Why this works

| Old approach | New approach |
|---|---|
| `adjustResize` (deprecated API 30) | `WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime()` |
| OS resizes the window | You read the keyboard height and pad the decor view |

The insets listener fires every time the keyboard opens/closes, giving you the exact pixel height. By padding the root `DecorView`, your entire MAUI layout (including the bottom input bar) gets pushed up automatically.

### iOS

iOS already handles this correctly via `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` (enabled by default in MAUI). If you still see issues on iOS, wrap your chat page content in a `ScrollView` so the auto-scroll manager can find and adjust it.
